  "title": "Junior Customer Events Executive (training provided)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>We are a fast-growing organization specializing in events, roadshows, and customer engagement campaigns. We focus on developing individuals through hands-on experience, structured training, and clear career progression.</p><p></p><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>As a Customer Service / Events Executive, you will represent our clients at events and promotional campaigns while delivering excellent customer experiences. This role is ideal for individuals who enjoy working with people and are eager to learn communication, branding, and sales-related skills.</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>* Support and execute events, roadshows, and marketing campaigns</p><p>* Engage customers professionally and represent client brands</p><p>* Deliver quality customer service and product information</p><p>* Assist in building and maintaining client relationships</p><p>* Work closely with team members to achieve campaign objectives</p><p></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>* Positive attitude with strong willingness to learn</p><p>* Good communication and interpersonal skills</p><p>* Able to work well in a team-oriented environment</p><p>* No prior experience required; training will be provided</p><p></p><p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p><p>* Structured training and skill development</p><p>* Clear career progression and leadership opportunities</p><p>* Performance-based incentives and bonuses</p><p>* Exposure to marketing, customer engagement, and events</p><p>* Supportive, inclusive, and dynamic team culture</p><p></p><p><strong>Career Level</strong></p><p>* Entry Level / Fresh Graduates / Career Switchers welcome</p><p></p><p>Interested candidates are encouraged to apply.</p>",
